ny was renamed \"Champion Knitting Mills Inc.\", producing [[Sweater|sweatshirts]]. Soon after, Champion products would be adopted by the [[United States Military Academy|US Military Academy]] to be used during training exercises and physical education classes.<ref name=champeu>[http://www.champion-eu.com/about-us About us] on Champion-eu website</ref>\n\nChampion was acquired by [[Sara Lee Corporation]] in 1989.<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/1989/02/14/business/champion-products-accepts-bid.html</ref> Champion produced uniforms for all the [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] teams during the 1990s and some [[National Football League|NFL]] teams during the 1970s to the 1990s, for both on-field and retail purposes. It has also produced sportswear for many major colleges.<ref>{{Citation|last=JARochNY|title=Abraham and William Feinbloom, Champion Products, Inc.|date=2010-10-21|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sayHwiulUA0|accessdate=2018-06-05}}</ref> Champion was also the kit manufacturer of the [[1992 United States men's Olympic basketball team|Olympic basketball team]] that competed at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=champeu/>\n\nFrom the mid-1980s to the mid-1990s, it was a very common fashion trend to see girls and guys of all ages wearing Champion sweatshirts over a turtleneck and over jeans with slouch socks and sneakers. Girls of all ages and adults also wore the sweatshirts oversized or extra-long with leggings and slouch socks and athletic sneakers, [[Keds]] or boat shoes. Today, Champion is now considered a very well known brand.\n\nFrom 2008, Champion produced kits for [[Premier League]] side, [[Wigan Athletic]], the [[Wales national football team]] and the jersey of the [[Greece national basketball team|Greek basketball team]],<ref>[http://www.champion-eu.com/news/en/62180/2/Champion_opens_it_s_100th_store_in_Faenza_Italy.aspx Champion presents the new Greek national basketball team jersey] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708134003/http://www.champion-eu.com/news/en/62180/2/Champion_opens_it_s_100th_store_in_Faenza_Italy.aspx |date=July 8, 2011 }}</ref> also [[Pallacanestro Cant\u00f9]], in Italy.\n\nFor many years Champion supplied the athletic uniforms for the [[University of Notre Dame|Notre Dame]] [[Fighting Irish]]. In 2001 Notre Dame signed a five-year exclusive agreement with [[Adidas]], which ended a partnership Champion had with the university that spanned over 50 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://magazine.nd.edu/news/16179-adidas-allegiance/|title=Adidas allegiance // News // Notre Dame Magazine // University of Notre Dame|last=Dame|first=ENR/PAZ // University Communications: Web // University of Notre|website=magazine.nd.edu|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref>\n\n==Sponsorships==\n{{More citations needed section|date=December 2019}}\nChampion has manufactured and provided kit uniforms for the following teams and associations:\n\n===Current sponsorships===\n\n\n=====Associations=====\n* [[FIBA]]<ref>[http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fc/FIBA/PartSpon/p/openNodeIDs/899/selNodeID/899/offiSpon.html FIBA global partners], retrieved 31 Aug 2014</ref>\n* [[National Basketball League (Australia)]] (effective 2020-21 season)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nbl.com.au/news/champion-signs-up-as-nbl-on-court-apparel-partner |website=NBL.com.au |publisher=National Basketball League |accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n=====National teams=====\n* {{Flag icon|Albania}} [[Albania national basketball team|Albania]]\n* {{Flag icon|South Africa}} [[South Africa national basketball team|South Africa]]\n\n=====Club teams=====\n* {{Flag icon|Serbia}} [[KK FMP Beograd|FMP]]\n* {{Flag icon|Croatia}} [[KK Zadar|Zadar]]\n* {{Flag icon|Serbia}} [[KK Dynamic|Dynamic VIP PAY]]\n\n====Lacrosse====\n* {{flagicon|USA}} [[US Lacrosse|USA national team]]\n\n===Past sponsorships===\n====American/Canadian football====\n* {{Flag icon|USA}} [[XFL (2001)|XFL]] (2001)\n* {{Flag icon|CAN}} [[Canadian Football League|CFL]] (1987\u201